longBusinessSummary: Security Bank Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, provides banking and financial products and services to wholesale and retail clients in the Philippines. It operates through Financial Markets, Wholesale Banking, Retail Banking, and All Other segments. The company's Financial Markets segment offers money market, foreign exchange, financial derivatives, securities distribution, asset management, and trust and fiduciary services. The Wholesale Banking segment provides relationship management, trade, cash management, deposit-taking, leasing, and structured financing services; and lending and other credit facilities, as well as advisory services relating to debt and equity capital raising, project financing, and mergers and acquisitions for corporate, institutional, and public sector markets. The company's Retail Banking segment is involved in deposit-taking and servicing activities; and providing commercial and consumer loans, credit card facilities, and bancassurance products for individual, retail, small-and-medium enterprise, and middle markets. It also provides a range of investment banking and financial services comprising equity underwriting, project finance, private placements, debt underwriting and syndication, financial advisory, mergers and acquisitions, privatization, investment and corporate advisory, and stock brokering services. In addition, the company rents, leases, and hires machineries and equipment, automotive equipment, automobiles, and a range of motor vehicles, as well as various land, air, or water transportation systems. As of December 31, 2018, it operated a network of 305 online branches and 760 automated teller machines. Security Bank Corporation was founded in 1951 and is headquartered in Makati, the Philippines.
